Overview
Like most website operators, AnkiApp Inc. collects, from AnkiApp users, non-personally-identifying information of the sort that web browsers and servers typically make available, such as the browser type, language preference, referring site, and the date and time of each visitor request. AnkiApp Inc.'s purpose in collecting non-personally identifying information is to better understand how visitors use its service. From time to time, AnkiApp Inc. may release non-personally-identifying information in the aggregate, e.g., by publishing a report on trends in the usage of its service. AnkiApp Inc. may use usage data, and any content you provide, to improve its services.
Email
AnkiApp Inc. may collect your email address, and use it to contact you, from time to time.
Study Groups
When you invite someone to a Study Group, or accept an invitation to a Study Group, your email address and information about your study progress will be shared with the other members of the group.
Protection of Certain Personally-Identifying Information
AnkiApp Inc. will not rent or sell potentially personally-identifying or personally-identifying information to anyone. AnkiApp Inc. only discloses potentially personally-identifying and personally-identifying information, without your permission, in response to a subpoena, court order or other governmental request. AnkiApp Inc. takes all measures reasonably necessary to protect against the unauthorized access, use, alteration or destruction of potentially personally-identifying and personally-identifying information.
Privacy Policy Changes
Although most changes are likely to be minor, AnkiApp Inc. may change this Privacy Policy from time to time, and at AnkiApp Inc.'s sole discretion. AnkiApp Inc. encourages users to frequently check this page for any changes to its Privacy Policy. Your continued use of AnkiApp after any change in this Privacy Policy will constitute your acceptance of such change.
